caption: Genuine Mexican street fare in a convenient Brooklyn location. Tacos to-go were flavorful and nicely packed, shrimp taco a standout.
Best shrimp tacos in the nbhood. Super fresh and done just right.
One of my favorite spots to grab some food. fantastic location, well kept, and fantastic customer service. A must try!

Quick delivery, affordable. I checked the no utensils & napkins box but they were still in the bag(not a big deal, but didn't pay attention to specific requirements) Food had good flavor but chicken was overly burnt on the grilled marks, very dissatisfying. I had to pick it out. If that wasn't the case I would've given it 4 stars.

I got shrimp quesadilla and it was so good! Shrimps in it were fresh and good-sized, and the cheese and the tortilla were good too. I also got fish taco and chicken taco. They were served with fresh lime wedges and sliced cucumber on the side. Overall the taste is not salty (which feels good for health) and feels fresh and authentic. Very good!

I ordered take out. Took a bit longer than expected for the food but very worth it. Chicken was delicious, well seasoned, and quite the opposite of dry. I liked their rice and beans a lot too, it’s way better than most places i’ve tried. The guacamole was really yummy and so were the little sauces that come with their family dinner deals. Also tried their hen soup and it was amazing. 10/10  Food tasted authentic and delicious

Hands down worst Mexican food I’ve ever had. I ordered the chicken tacos with lettuce, tomatoes and avocado on top. They gave me 2 tortillas with about 2 tablespoons of meat, a single 1” piece of lettuce, and didn’t include the cilantro it comes with. Put a pile of guac on top instead of avocado. My friend ordered a torta which was clearly reheated, and the chicken was yellow. He also pulled a hair out of it, just now. Tried to call the restaurant and the server put the phone down after I told her what happened. after 10 minutes of waiting I hung up and tried to call back but they did not answer. They did not offer a refund or to send something else.
Good food, good service. Small restaurant and cash only, but definitely worth it.

Made an order online and it came on time; however, I was given the complete wrong order. Called the restaurant to inform them that I received an incorrect order. She did not apologise, but asked if I wanted another order... I responded by saying yes I would like MY order. She seemed a bit hesitant to do so but said sure and hung up. I waited an hour and twenty minutes so I called them back to ask how much longer it would be, turns out they had closed for the night. I then called GrubHub and the agent informed me that the restaurant issued me a refund that would take 3-5 business days. They did not reach out to me to let me know that they would not be delivering my food anymore, after they said they would. I waited over an hour like a fool ... Thanks. Worst. Restaurant. Ever.

Delightful!! With tons of Mexican Restuarants popping up all over Brooklyn,  this simple place stands the test of time. Ordered a shrimp quesadilla and was feeling totally guilty about the consuming so much cheese,  but it was everything it was suppose to be, "Authentic" it even came with a small side of sour cream and guacomole. Great price point and they have a pretty lengthy menu. The location is perfect and they even have a few tables and chairs outdoors. I will definitely be back!

3.5 stars. I sure miss Chicago’s Pilsen neighborhood. Mexican food is scarce here in comparison. Mi Tierra is a decent option for extremely fast delivered and adequate Mexican fare. Flavors are a bit diluted and Americanized but we’re living in a “Chipotle” world now aren’t we. I’ll order here again.

Simple, family-run spot strikes a good balance. Mexican favorites plus other menu options draw a steady stream of locals. Mi Tierra burrito with carnitas was large and tasty. Great service, no frills, just right.
Awesome burrito, great price, great staff. 100% coming back.
